        "solution": "<p>$|x-y| \\leq y \\leq 4 \\sqrt{x}$</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m9z8ryuu/70144256-859e-47e3-9f8e-df5ee6654f2e/1b8b7470-232d-11f0-99e8-5f2c09d57200/file-jaoe38c1m9z8ryuv.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m9z8ryuu/70144256-859e-47e3-9f8e-df5ee6654f2e/1b8b7470-232d-11f0-99e8-5f2c09d57200/file-jaoe38c1m9z8ryuv.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2025 (Online) 3rd April Evening Shift Mathematics - Area Under The Curves Question 20 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>$$\\begin{aligned}\n&amp; \\text { Area }=\\int_0^{64}\\left(4 \\sqrt{x}-\\frac{x}{2}\\right) d x \\\\\n&amp; \\left.=\\frac{4 x^{3 / 2}}{\\frac{3}{2}}-\\frac{x^2}{4}\\right]_0^{64}\n\\end{aligned}$$</p>",
