        "solution": "<picture><source media=\"(max-width: 320px)\" srcset=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1ktcsg3cd/1ed86c78-60f7-45c1-b20b-cdaab85cab73/c13e42c0-1158-11ec-9e37-4f17600f489e/file-1ktcsg3ce-320w.jpeg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 500px)\" srcset=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1ktcsg3cd/1ed86c78-60f7-45c1-b20b-cdaab85cab73/c13e42c0-1158-11ec-9e37-4f17600f489e/file-1ktcsg3ce-500w.jpeg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 680px)\" srcset=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1ktcsg3cd/1ed86c78-60f7-45c1-b20b-cdaab85cab73/c13e42c0-1158-11ec-9e37-4f17600f489e/file-1ktcsg3ce-680w.jpeg\"><img src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1ktcsg3cd/1ed86c78-60f7-45c1-b20b-cdaab85cab73/c13e42c0-1158-11ec-9e37-4f17600f489e/file-1ktcsg3ce.jpeg\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"JEE Main 2021 (Online) 26th August Morning Shift Mathematics - Area Under The Curves Question 112 English Explanation\"></picture> <br><br>For A &amp; B<br><br>3x<sup>2</sup> = 6x + 24 $$\\Rightarrow$$ x<sup>2</sup> $$-$$ 2x $$-$$ 8 = 0<br><br>$$\\Rightarrow$$ x = $$-$$2, 4<br><br>Area $$ = \\int\\limits_{ - 2}^4 {\\left( {{3 \\over 2}x + 6 - {3 \\over 4}{x^2}} \\right)dx} $$<br><br>$$ = \\left[ {{{3{x^2}} \\over 4} + 6x - {{{x^3}} \\over 4}} \\right]_{ - 2}^4 = 27$$",
        "marks": 4,
