        "correctOptionIndex": 2,
        "correctAnswer": "",
        "solution": "y =  (x – 1)[x] = $$\\left\\{ {\\matrix{\n   {0,} &amp; {0 \\le x &lt; 1}  \\cr \n   {x - 1,} &amp; {1 \\le x &lt; 2}  \\cr \n   {2,} &amp; {x = 2}  \\cr \n\n } } \\right.$$\n<br><img src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/jgy2xukh0vpjlu/491c02ed-5785-4f16-aecd-8155bb7a7f1c/8322f620-1d39-11eb-8293-3b6cc591631c/file-jgy2xukh0vpjlv-473w.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"JEE Main 2020 (Online) 5th September Evening Slot Mathematics - Area Under The Curves Question 127 English Explanation\">\n<br><br>A = $$\\int\\limits_0^2 {2\\sqrt x } dx - {1 \\over 2}.1.1$$\n<br><br>= 2$$\\left[ {{{{x^{3/2}}} \\over {{3 \\over 2}}}} \\right]_0^2$$ - $${1 \\over 2}$$\n<br><br>= $${{8\\sqrt 2 } \\over 3} - {1 \\over 2}$$",
