        "year": 2013,
        "difficulty": "Medium",
        "type": "SCQ",
        "question": "The area (in square units) bounded by the curves $$y = \\sqrt {x,}  $$ $$2y - x + 3 = 0,$$ $$x$$-axis, and lying in the first quadrant is : ",
