        "solution": "The graph of the curve $$y = {\\log _e}\\left( {x + e} \\right)$$ is as shown in the fig.\n<br><br><img class=\"question-image\" src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/qRBC0p0qWgadMfx1J/L9ACfidrRjv05IgnVECrgrkf7dAnB/3puEOe7zAMZ4zlRMilZJqy/image.png\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"AIEEE 2005 Mathematics - Area Under The Curves Question 167 English Explanation\"> \n<br><br>Required area \n<br><br>$$A = \\int\\limits_{1 - e}^0 {ydx}  = \\int\\limits_{1 - e}^0 {{{\\log }_e}} \\left( {x + e} \\right)dx$$\n<br><br>put $$x + e = t \\Rightarrow dx = dt$$\n<br><br>also At $$x = 1 - e,t = 1$$\n<br><br>At $$x = 0,\\,\\,t = e$$ \n<br><br>$$\\therefore$$  $$A = \\int\\limits_1^e {{{\\log }_e}} \\,tdt = \\left[ {t\\,{{\\log }_e}t - t_1^e} \\right]$$\n<br><br>$$e - e - 0 + 1 = 1$$\n<br><br>Hence the required area is $$1$$ square unit. ",
