        "question": "The value of '$$a$$' for which one root of the quadratic equation \n$$$\\left( {{a^2} - 5a + 3} \\right){x^2} + \\left( {3a - 1} \\right)x + 2 = 0$$$\n\nis twice as large as the other is",
