        "year": "JEE Main 2018 (online 16th april morning slot)",
        "difficulty": "Medium",
        "question": "Let p, q and r be real numbers (p $$ \\ne $$ q,  r $$ \\ne $$ 0), such that the roots of the equation $${1 \\over {x + p}} + {1 \\over {x + q}} = {1 \\over r}$$ are equal in  magnitude but opposite in sign, then the sum of squares of these roots is equal to :",
