        "solution": "Given, \n\n$${1 \\over {x + p}} + {1 \\over {x + q}} = {1 \\over r}$$\n\n$$ \\Rightarrow $$$$\\,\\,\\,$$ $${{x + p + x + q} \\over {\\left( {x + p} \\right)\\left( {x + q} \\right)}} = {1 \\over r}$$\n\n$$ \\Rightarrow $$$$\\,\\,\\,$$ (2x + p + q) r = x2 + px + qx + pq\n\n$$ \\Rightarrow $$$$\\,\\,\\,$$ x2 + (p + q $$-$$ 2r) x + pq $$-$$ pr $$-$$ qr = 0\n\nLet $$\\alpha $$ and $$\\beta $$ are the roots, \n\n$$\\therefore\\,\\,\\,$$ $$\\alpha $$ + $$\\beta $$ = $$-$$ (p + q $$-$$ 2r)\n\nand $$\\alpha $$ $$\\beta $$ = pq $$-$$ pr $$-$$ qr\n\nGiven that,  $$\\alpha $$ = $$-$$ $$\\beta $$ $$ \\Rightarrow $$ $$\\alpha $$\n + $$\\beta $$ = 0\n\n$$\\therefore\\,\\,\\,$$ $$-$$ (p + q $$-$$ 2r) = 0\n\nNow, $$\\alpha $$2 + $$\\beta $$2\n\n= ($$\\alpha $$ + $$\\beta $$)2 $$-$$ 2$$\\alpha $$ $$\\beta $$\n\n= ($$-$$ (p + q $$-$$ 2r))2  $$-$$ 2 (pq $$-$$ pr $$-$$ qr)\n\n= p2 +q2 + 4r2 + 2pq $$-$$ 4pr $$-$$ 4qr $$-$$  2pq + 2pr + 2qr\n\n= p2 + q2 + 4r2 $$-$$ 2pr $$-$$ 2qr\n\n= p2 + q2 $$-$$ 2r (p + q $$-$$ 2r)\n\n= p2 + q2 $$-$$  2r (0)\n\n= p2 + q2",
