        "question": "If $$\\alpha $$, $$\\beta $$ and $$\\gamma $$ are three consecutive terms of a non-constant G.P. such that the equations $$\\alpha $$x\n2\n + 2$$\\beta $$x + $$\\gamma $$ = 0 and\nx2\n + x – 1 = 0 have a common root, then $$\\alpha $$($$\\beta $$ + $$\\gamma $$) is equal to :",
