        "difficulty": "Medium",
        "question": "Let $$\\lambda  \\ne 0$$  be in R. If $$\\alpha $$ and $$\\beta $$ are the roots of the \nequation, x2 - x + 2$$\\lambda $$ = 0 and $$\\alpha $$ and $$\\gamma $$ are the roots of \nthe equation, $$3{x^2} - 10x + 27\\lambda  = 0$$, then $${{\\beta \\gamma } \\over \\lambda }$$  is equal to:",
