        "question": "Let $$\\alpha $$ and $$\\beta $$ be two real roots of the equation \n(k + 1)tan2x - $$\\sqrt 2 $$ . $$\\lambda $$tanx = (1 - k), where k($$ \\ne $$ - 1)\nand $$\\lambda $$ are real numbers. if tan2 ($$\\alpha $$ + $$\\beta $$) = 50, then a value of $$\\lambda $$ is:",
