        "correctOptionIndex": 1,
        "solution": "$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& x|x|-5|x+2|+6=0 \\\\\\\\\n& \\text { Case-I : } \\\\\\\\\n& \\text { When } xCase-II :\n\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& \\text { When } -2 \\leq x Case-III :\n\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& \\text { When } x \\geq 0 \\text { then } \\\\\\\\\n& x^2-5(x+2)+6=0 \\\\\\\\\n\\Rightarrow & x^2-5 x-4=0 \\\\\\\\\n& x=\\frac{5 \\pm \\sqrt{25+16}}{2} \\\\\\\\\n& =\\frac{5 \\pm \\sqrt{41}}{2} \\\\\\\\\n& x=\\frac{5 - \\sqrt{41}}{2} \\text { is accepted } \\\\\\\\\n\\therefore  & 3 \\text { real roots are possible. }\n\\end{aligned}\n$$",
