        "questionId": "pyq_1lgpxzk6k",
        "year": "JEE Main 2023 (online 13th april morning shift)",
        "difficulty": "Hard",
        "question": "The set of all $$a \\in \\mathbb{R}$$ for which the equation $$x|x-1|+|x+2|+a=0$$ has exactly one real root, is :",
        "options": [
          "$$(-\\infty, \\infty)$$",
          "$$(-6, \\infty)$$",
          "$$(-\\infty,-3)$$",
          "$$(-6,-3)$$"
        ],
        "correctOptionIndex": 0,
        "solution": "$$\nx|x-1|+|x+2|+a=0\n$$\n\nCase I : If $x<-2$ then\n\n$$\n-x^2+x-x-2+a=0\n$$\n\n$$\na=x^2+2\n$$\n\n$y=x^2+2$ is decreasing $\\forall x \\in(-\\infty,-2)$\n\nCase II : If $-2 \\leq x<1$ then\n\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& -x^2+x+x+2+a=0 \\\\\\\\\n& a=x^2-2 x-2\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\n\n$y=x^2-2 x-2$ is decreasing $\\forall x \\in[-2,1)$.\n\nCase III: If $x \\geq 1$ then\n\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& x^2-x+x+2+a=0 \\\\\\\\\n& a=-\\left(x^2+2\\right)\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\n\n$y=-\\left(x^2+2\\right)$ is decreasing $\\forall x \\in[1, \\infty)$\n\n$\\therefore$ Exactly one real root $\\forall x \\in R$",
