        "difficulty": "Medium",
        "question": "Let $$\\alpha, \\beta ; \\alpha>\\beta$$, be the roots of the equation $$x^2-\\sqrt{2} x-\\sqrt{3}=0$$. Let $$\\mathrm{P}_n=\\alpha^n-\\beta^n, n \\in \\mathrm{N}$$. Then $$(11 \\sqrt{3}-10 \\sqrt{2}) \\mathrm{P}_{10}+(11 \\sqrt{2}+10) \\mathrm{P}_{11}-11 \\mathrm{P}_{12}$$ is equal to",
