        "difficulty": "Medium",
        "question": "Let $$\\alpha, \\beta$$ be roots of $$x^2+\\sqrt{2} x-8=0$$. If $$\\mathrm{U}_{\\mathrm{n}}=\\alpha^{\\mathrm{n}}+\\beta^{\\mathrm{n}}$$, then $$\\frac{\\mathrm{U}_{10}+\\sqrt{2} \\mathrm{U}_9}{2 \\mathrm{U}_8}$$ is equal to ________.",
