        "year": "JEE Main 2024 (online 6th april morning shift)",
        "difficulty": "Hard",
        "question": "Let $$x_1, x_2, x_3, x_4$$ be the solution of the equation $$4 x^4+8 x^3-17 x^2-12 x+9=0$$ and $$\\left(4+x_1^2\\right)\\left(4+x_2^2\\right)\\left(4+x_3^2\\right)\\left(4+x_4^2\\right)=\\frac{125}{16} m$$. Then the value of $$m$$ is _________.",
        "options": [
          "Answer: 221"
        ],
        "correctOptionIndex": 0,
        "solution": "First, observe that for a degree-4 polynomial  \n\n$$P(x)=4x^4+8x^3-17x^2-12x+9$$  \n\nwith roots $x_1,\\dots,x_4$, we have  \n\n$$\\prod_{i=1}^4(x_i^2+4) =\\prod_{i=1}^4\\bigl[(x_i-2i)(x_i+2i)\\bigr] =\\frac{P(2i)\\,P(-2i)}{4^2}\\,. $$\n\nCompute $P(2i)$:  \n\n$      P(2i)      =4(2i)^4+8(2i)^3-17(2i)^2-12(2i)+9      =64-64i+68-24i+9      =141-88i.    $\n\nBy conjugation,  \n\n$      P(-2i)=141+88i.    $\n\nHence  \n\n$      \\prod_{i=1}^4(x_i^2+4)      =\\frac{(141-88i)(141+88i)}{16}      =\\frac{141^2+88^2}{16}      =\\frac{19881+7744}{16}      =\\frac{27625}{16}.    $\n\nWe are told  \n\n$      \\prod_{i=1}^4(x_i^2+4)=\\frac{125}{16}\\,m      =\\frac{27625}{16},    $  \n\nso  \n\n$      125\\,m=27625      \\quad\\Longrightarrow\\quad      m=221.    $\n\nAnswer: $ \\displaystyle 221.$",
