        "difficulty": "Medium",
        "question": "Let $\\alpha$ and $\\beta$ be the roots of the equation $p x^2+q x-r=0$, where $p \\neq 0$. If $p, q$ and $r$ be the consecutive terms of a non constant G.P. and $\\frac{1}{\\alpha}+\\frac{1}{\\beta}=\\frac{3}{4}$, then the value of $(\\alpha-\\beta)^2$ is :",
