        "difficulty": "Easy",
        "question": "If $\\alpha, \\beta$, where $\\alpha<\\beta$, are the roots of the equation $\\lambda x^2-(\\lambda+3) x+3=0$ such that $\\frac{1}{\\alpha}-\\frac{1}{\\beta}=\\frac{1}{3}$, then the sum of all possible values of $\\lambda$ is",
